#. Tag: title
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Beskrivelse"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdesu; is a graphical front end for the &UNIX; <command>su</command> "
"command for the K Desktop Environment. It allows you to run a program as "
"different user by supplying the password for that user. &kdesu; is an "
"unprivileged program; it uses the system's <command>su</command>."
msgstr ""
"&kdesu; er en grafisk front for &UNIX;-kommanoden <command>su</command> for "
"K desktopmiljøet. Det tillader dig at køre et program som en anden  bruger "
"ved at angive kodeordet for denne bruger. &kdesu; er ikke et priviligeret "
"program; det bruger systemets <command>su</command>."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdesu; has one additional feature: it can optionally remember passwords for "
"you. If you are using this feature, you only need to enter the password once "
"for each command."
msgstr ""
"&kdesu; har yderligere en egenskab: du kan vælge at det skal huske kodeord "
"for dig. Hvis du bruger dette, er du kun nødt til at indtaste kodeordet en "
"gang for hver kommando."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This program is meant to be started from the command line or from <filename>."
"desktop</filename> files."
msgstr ""
"Dette program er beregnet til at blive startet fra kommandolinjen eller fra "
"<filename>.desktop</filename>-filer."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since <command>kdesu</command> is no longer installed in <userinput> $(kf5-"
"config --prefix)</userinput>/bin but in <userinput>kf5-config --path "
"libexec</userinput> and therefore not in your <envar>Path</envar>, you have "
"to use <userinput>$(kf5-config --path libexec)<command>kdesu</command></"
"userinput> to launch <command>kdesu</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options"
msgstr "Tilvalg"

#. Tag: option
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:79
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "-c <replaceable>program</replaceable>"
msgid "-c <replaceable>command</replaceable>"
msgstr "-c <replaceable>program</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:80
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This specifies the program to run as root. It has to be passed in one "
#| "argument. So if, for example, you want to start a new file manager, you "
#| "would enter at the prompt: <userinput><command>kdesu <option>-c "
#| "<replaceable>kfm -sw</replaceable></option></command></userinput>"
msgid ""
"This specifies the command to run as root. It has to be passed in one "
"argument. So if, for example, you want to start a new file manager, you "
"would enter at the prompt: <userinput>$(kf5-config --path "
"libexec)<command>kdesu <option>-c <replaceable> &dolphin;</replaceable></"
"option></command></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Dette angiver programmet der skal køres som root. Det skal gives som et "
"argument. Så hvis, for eksempel, du ønsker at starte en ny fulhåndtering, "
"vil du skrive ved prompten: <userinput><command>kdesu <option>-c "
"<replaceable>kfm -sw</replaceable></option></command></userinput>"

#. Tag: option
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-d</option>"
msgstr "<option>-d</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show debug information."
msgstr "Vis fejlinformation."

#. Tag: option
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:90
#, no-c-format
msgid "-f <replaceable>file</replaceable>"
msgstr "-f <replaceable>fil</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option allow efficient use of &kdesu; in <filename>.desktop</filename> "
"files. It tells &kdesu; to examine the file specified by <parameter>file</"
"parameter>. If this file is writable by the current user, &kdesu; will "
"execute the command as the current user. If it is not writable, the command "
"is executed as user <parameter>user</parameter> (defaults to root)."
msgstr ""
"Dette tillader effektiv brug af &kdesu; i <filename>.desktop</filename>-"
"filer. Det beder &kdesu; om at undersøge filen angivet ved <parameter>file</"
"parameter>. Hvis denne fil er skrivbar for nuværende bruger, vil &kdesu; "
"køre kommandoen som nuværende bruger. Hvis dette ikke er tilfældet vil den "
"køres som brugeren <parameter>bruger</parameter> (som standard root)."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:97
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<parameter>file</parameter> is evaluated like this: if <parameter>file</"
#| "parameter> starts with a <literal>/</literal>, it is taken as an absolute "
#| "filename. Otherwise, it is taken as the name of a global &kde; "
#| "configuration file. For example: to configure the K display manager, "
#| "<application>kdm</application>, you could issue <command>kdesu <option>-c "
#| "kdmconfig -f kdmrc</option></command>"
msgid ""
"<parameter>file</parameter> is evaluated like this: if <parameter>file</"
"parameter> starts with a <literal>/</literal>, it is taken as an absolute "
"filename. Otherwise, it is taken as the name of a global &kde; configuration "
"file."
msgstr ""
"<parameter>fil</parameter> evalueres sådan her: hvis <parameter>fil</"
"parameter> starter med et <literal>/</literal>, opfattes det som et absolut "
"filnavn. Ellers opfattes det som navnet på en global indstillingsfil for "
"&kde;. For eksempel: For at indstille <application>kdm</application>, kunne "
"du skrive <command>kdesu <option>-c kdmconfig -f kdmrc</option></command>"

#. Tag: term
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-i</option> <replaceable>icon name</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-i</option> <replaceable>ikonnavn</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify icon to use in the password dialog. You may specify just the name, "
"without any extension."
msgstr ""
"Angiv ikon at bruge i kodeordsdialogen. Du kan angive kun navnet, uden nogen "
"filendelse."

#. Tag: option
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-n</option>"
msgstr "<option>-n</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do not keep the password. This disables the <guilabel>keep password</"
"guilabel> checkbox in the password dialog."
msgstr ""
"Husk ikke kodeordet. Dette deaktiverer <guilabel>husk kodeord</guilabel> "
"afkrydsningsfeltet i kodeordsdialogen."

#. Tag: term
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-p</option> <replaceable>priority</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-p</option> <replaceable>prioritet</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set priority value. The priority is an arbitrary number between 0 and 100, "
"where 100 means highest priority, and 0 means lowest. The default is 50."
msgstr ""
"Angiv prioritetsværdi. Prioriteten er et vilkårligt tal mellem 0 og 100, "
"hvor 100 betyder højeste prioritet, og 0 betyder mindste. Standardværdien er "
"50."

#. Tag: option
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-r</option>"
msgstr "<option>-r</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use realtime scheduling."
msgstr "Brug realtidsskemalægning"

#. Tag: option
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-s</option>"
msgstr "<option>-s</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Stop the kdesu daemon. This is the daemon that caches successful passwords "
"in the background. This feature may also be disabled with <option>-n</"
"option> when &kdesu; is initially run."
msgstr ""
"Stop kdesu-dæmonen. Dette er dæmonen der cacher kodeord der lykkedes i "
"baggrunden. Denne funktion kan også deaktiveres med <option>-n</option> når "
"&kdesu; først køres."

#. Tag: option
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-t</option>"
msgstr "<option>-t</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enable terminal output. This disables password keeping. This is largely for "
"debugging purposes; if you want to run a console mode app, use the standard "
"<command>su</command> instead."
msgstr ""
"Aktivér terminaluddata. Dette deaktiverer det at huske kodeordet. Det er "
"stort set til fejlsøgningsformål; hvis du ønsker at køre et program i "
"konsoltilstand, kan du i stedet bruge <command>su</command>-kommandoen."

#. Tag: term
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-u</option> <replaceable> user</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-u</option> <replaceable> bruger</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kdesu.1.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While the most common use for &kdesu; is to run a command as the superuser, "
"you can supply any user name and the appropriate password."
msgstr ""
"Selvom den almindeligste brug af &kdesu; er at køre et kommando som "
"systemadministrator, kan du angive et hvilket som helst brugernavn og "
"passende kodeord."

